name: Jenkins Classic
description: Jenkins is an open source automation server for automating tasks related to building, testing, and delivering software. The Sumo Logic App for Jenkins helps you monitor build successes, failures, and performance. The preconfigured dashboards provide insight into current current and recent build activity.

children.name: Jenkins Classic - Overview
children.description: The Jenkins Classic - Overview dashboard provides relation between job and Executors on a Jenkins master. Dashboard helps you to relate job run duration, status, physical memory, disk memory, unused machine.

panels.name: Disk Memory
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| where [subquery from=(-2d): $$logsrc  (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| json field=_raw "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor" as Disk_Space nodrop
| parse regex field=Disk_Space "(?<Disk_Space>.*?) (?<Unit>.*[A-Z]+)" nodrop
| where !isEmpty(Disk_Space)
| num(Disk_Space)
| if(Unit in ("MB", "Mb", "mb"), Disk_Space/1024, if(Unit in ("KB", "Kb", "kb"), Disk_Space/1024/1024, if(Unit in ("TB", "Tb", "tb"), Disk_Space*1024, Disk_Space))) as Disk_Space
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| avg(Disk_Space) as Average, max(Disk_Space) as Maximum, min(Disk_Space) as Minimum by _timeslice
| fields _timeslice, Average, Minimum, Maximum
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})
| fields - Maximum, Minimum, Minimum_1d, Maximum_1d

Executors
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "numberOfExecutors", "nodeName", "nodeLabel", "numberOfFreeExecutors", "eventTime" as Total_Executors, NodeName, NodeLabel, Free_Executors, Event_Time nodrop
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}

| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop

panels.name: Physical Memory Use Percentage
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| where [subquery from=(-2d): $$logsrc  (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| json "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "nodeLabel"  as SwapMemory, Node_Label nodrop
| parse field=SwapMemory "Memory:*  Swap:*" as Physical_Memory, Swap_Memory
| parse regex field=Physical_Memory "(?<Used_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Memory>.*?)[A-Z]"
| (Used_Memory/Total_Memory)*100 as Used_Memory
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| avg(Used_Memory) as Average, max(Used_Memory) as Maximum, min(Used_Memory) as Minimum by _timeslice
| fields _timeslice, Average, Minimum, Maximum
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})
| fields - Minimum, Maximum, Minimum_1d, Maximum_1d

panels.name: Jobs in Queue
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Queue_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "jobName" as Name
| first(_raw) by Name, Master
| json field = _first "queueId", "queueTime", "isBlocked", "reasonForBlock", "isConcurrentBuild", "jobName", "jobURL" as %"Queue Id", %"Queue Time(sec)", Blocked, Reason, %"Concurrent Build", Name, URL nodrop
| tourl(URL, Name) as Name
| replace (URL, /\/[0-9]{1,}/, "") as URL
| where ![subquery : $$logsrc  "logType":"Job_Status"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "jobBuildURL" as URL
| replace (URL, /\/[0-9]{1,}/, "") as URL
| count by URL, Master
| compose URL, Master]
| count by Master, %"Queue Time(sec)", Name, Blocked, Reason
| fields - _count

search.queryText:

| count by Log_Time, Job_Name, Build_Number, Stage_Name, Log_Message

panels.name: Job Parameters
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Job_Status {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number", "jobMetaData", "jobStartTime", "triggerCauses" as Name, Number, jobMetaData, jobStartTime, triggerCauses nodrop
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| replace (jobMetaData, "{", "{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"") as jobMetaData
| replace (jobMetaData, "\",", "\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"") as jobMetaData
| replace (jobMetaData, "}", "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t}") as jobMetaData
| concat("JOB START TIME\t\t - \t", jobStartTime, "\n\nTRIGGER CAUSES\t - \t", triggerCauses, "\n\nJOB PARAMETERS\t - \t", jobMetaData) as %"Job Run Information"
| count by %"Job Run Information"
| fields %"Job Run Information"

panels.name: Test Cases Distribution
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  "logType":"Job_Status" {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number" as Name, Number
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| json "testResult"
| parse regex field=testResult "\"(?<Key>.*?)\":(?<Value>.*?)[,}]" multi
| where key in ("skips", "failures", "passes")
| fields key, Value
| avg(Value) by Key

panels.name: Most Recent Console Logs
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc 
| _sourceHost as Master
| _sourceName as SourceName
| where SourceName matches "{{Name}}#{{Number}}*"
| parse field=_raw "[*] *" as Time, %"Log Message"
| trim (%"Log Message")
| count by Time, Master, %"Log Message"
| sort by Time
| fields Time, Master, %"Log Message"
| limit 50

panels.name: Error, Warning, Exception
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc 
| _sourceHost as Master
| _sourceName as SourceName
| where SourceName matches "{{Name}}#{{Number}}*"
| parse field=_raw "[*] *" as Time, %"Log Message"
| trim (%"Log Message")
| where %"Log Message" matches "*WARNING*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*ERROR*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*fail*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*warning*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*error*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*fail*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*Exception*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*Fail*" OR %"Log Message" matches "*Error*"
| count by Time, Master, %"Log Message"
| sort by Time
| fields Time, Master, %"Log Message"
| limit 20

panels.name: Configuration Change before Build
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  (Job_Started OR Config_Change) {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| {{Number}} as Build_Number
| join (json "eventTime", "message" as FirstEventTime, FirstMessage|parse field=FirstMessage "User * started the job * with build number as *." as FirstUser, FirstJobName, FirstBuildNumber | where FirstBuildNumber = Build_Number|fields FirstJobName, FirstEventTime) as firstStart,  
(json "eventTime", "message" as SecondEventTime, SecondMessage|parse field=SecondMessage "User * started the job * with build number as *." as SecondUser, SecondJobName, SecondBuildNumber |where SecondBuildNumber = Build_Number-1| fields SecondJobName, SecondEventTime) as SecondStart,
(json "userId", "userName", "eventTime", "message", "fileDetails.Old_File_Data", "fileDetails.Current_File_Data" as ConfigChangeUserId, ConfigChangeUserName, ConfigChangeEventtime, ConfigChangeMessage, Old_File_Data, Current_File_Data nodrop|parse field=ConfigChangeMessage "* changed configuration for the file jobs/*/config.xml." as ConfigChangeUser, ConfigChangeJobName | fields ConfigChangeUserId, ConfigChangeUserName, ConfigChangeJobName, ConfigChangeEventtime, Old_File_Data, Current_File_Data) as Config_Change
on firstStart.FirstJobName = SecondStart.SecondJobName AND firstStart.FirstJobName = Config_Change.ConfigChangeJobName 
| where Config_Change_ConfigChangeEventtime < firstStart_FirstEventTime AND Config_Change_ConfigChangeEventtime > SecondStart_SecondEventTime
| base64Decode(Config_Change_Old_File_Data) as %"Old File Data"
| base64Decode(Config_Change_Current_File_Data) as %"Current File Data"
| Config_Change_ConfigChangeUserId as %"User Id"
| Config_Change_ConfigChangeUserName as %"User Name"
| Config_Change_ConfigChangeEventtime as Time
| count by Time, %"User Id", %"User Name"
| fields Time, %"User Id", %"User Name"

panels.name: Job Run Duration
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Job_Status {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number", "jobRunDuration" as Name, Number, Duration
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| Duration/60 as Duration
| avg(Duration) as %"Duration in minutes" by Number
| fields %"Duration in minutes"

panels.name: Top 10 Slowest Tests
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Test_Result {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number" as Name, Number
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| json "testResult" as statusValues
| parse regex field=statusValues "(?<TestResult>\{[^\}]+\})" multi
| json auto field=TestResult
| className as %"Class Name" | testName as %"Test Name"| duration/60 as Duration | status as %"Test Status"
| concat(%"Class Name",".",%"Test Name") as %"Test Name"
| Duration/60 as Duration
| sum(Duration) as %"Test Duration in minutes" by %"Test Name"
| sort by %"Test Duration in minutes"
| limit 10

panels.name: Failed Tests
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Test_Result {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number" as Name, Number
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| json "testResult" as statusValues
| parse regex field=statusValues "(?<TestResult>\{[^\}]+\})" multi
| json auto field=TestResult
| where status="Failed"
| className as %"Class Name" | testName as %"Test Name"| duration/60 as %"Test Duration" | status as %"Test Status"
| errorStackTrace as %"Error Stack Trace"| errorDetails as %"Error Details"
| count by Master, %"Class Name", %"Test Name", %"Test Duration", %"Error Stack Trace", %"Error Details"
|fields - _count

panels.name: Job URLs
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Job_Status {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number", "jobBuildURL", "upstreamJobURL" as Name, Number, URL, UpStreamURL
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| if(isEmpty(URL) ,"", tourl(URL, concat("Build URL - ", name))) as %"Build URL"
| parse field=URL "*://*/" as domain, url_base nodrop
| if(isEmpty(UpStreamURL) ,"", tourl(concat(domain, "://",url_base,"/",UpStreamURL), concat("UpStream URL - ", name))) as %"Upstream Build URL"
| replace(URL, concat("/",number,"/"), "") as Config_URL
| concat(Config_URL, "/configure") as Config_URL
| tourl(Config_URL, concat("Config URL - ", name)) as %"Configuration URL"
| count by Master, %"Build URL", %"Upstream Build URL", %"Configuration URL"
| fields Master, %"Build URL", %"Upstream Build URL", %"Configuration URL"

panels.name: Build Information

$$logsrc  Job_Status {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number", "hudsonVersion", "label", "result", "description", "jobType", "user", "nodeName" as Name, number, hudsonVersion, Label, Result, Description, JobType, User, NodeName nodrop
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| if(Result matches "SUCCESS", ":white-heavy-check-mark:", ":prohibited:") as icon
| lookup utf as Result from https://s3.amazonaws.com/sumologic-app-data/emoji.csv on shortname=icon
| concat(concat("NAME				 - 	", Name, "

MASTER			 - 	", Master, "

NUMBER			 - 	",Number ,"

HUDSON VERSION	 - 	", hudsonVersion),
"

LABEL				 - 	", Label
,"

RESULT				 - 	", Result, "

DESCRIPTION		 - 	", Description, "

JOB TYPE			 - 	", JobType, "

STARTED BY			 - 	", User, "

NODE NAME			 - 	", NodeName) as %"Job Basic Information"
| count by %"Job Basic Information"
| fields %"Job Basic Information"

panels.name: Status
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Job_Status {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number", "result" as Name, Number, Result
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| where Result != "SUCCESS"
| count by Result
| fields - _count

panels.name: Top 5 Slowest Stages
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Pipeline_Stages {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number" as Name, Number
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| json "stages" as StagesPipeline
| parse regex field = StagesPipeline "(?<json_added_blob>\{[^\}]+(?:\}\}|\}))" multi
| json field=json_added_blob "id", "stageId", "name", "startTime", "duration", "status", "steps", "error" as ID, %"Stage ID", %"Stage Name", %"Start Time", %"Stage Duration", %"Stage Status", %"Stage Steps", %"Stage Error" nodrop
| sum(%"Stage Duration") as %"Stage Duration in seconds" by %"Stage Name"
| sort by  %"Stage Duration in seconds"
| limit 5

panels.name: SCM Information
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Scm_Status {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "jobName", "buildNumber", "scmURLs", "branches", "scmType", "revision" as Name, Number, scmURLs, branches, scmType, revision
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| replace(scmURLs, "git ", "") as scmURLs
| replace(scmURLs, " ", "\n") as scmURLs
| replace(branches, " ", "\n") as branches 
| concat("SCM TYPE\t - \t", scmType, "\n\nSCM URLs\t - \t",scmURLs,"\n\nREVISION\t - \t" ,revision,"\n\nBRANCHES\t - \t", branches) as %"Scm Information"
| count by %"Scm Information"
| fields %"Scm Information"

panels.name: Pipeline Stage Details
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Pipeline_Stages {{Name}}
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "name", "number" as Name, Number
| where Name = {{Name}} AND Number = {{Number}}
| json "stages" as StagesPipeline   
| parse regex field = StagesPipeline "(?<json_added_blob>\{[^\}]+(?:\}\}|\}))" multi
| json field=json_added_blob "id", "stageId", "name", "startTime", "duration", "status", "steps", "error" as ID, %"Stage ID", %"Stage Name", %"Start Time", %"Stage Duration", %"Stage Status", %"Stage Steps", %"Stage Error" nodrop
| where %"Stage Status" matches {{StageStatus}}
| replace (%"Stage Error", ",", "\n\n") as %"Stage Error"
| replace (%"Stage Steps", ",\"", "\n\n") as %"Stage Steps"
| replace (%"Stage Steps", ",", "\n") as %"Stage Steps"
| count by ID, %"Stage ID", %"Stage Name", %"Start Time", %"Stage Status", %"Stage Duration", %"Stage Error", %"Stage Steps"
| tolong(ID) as ID

panels.name: Available Disk Space (GB)
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| where ![subquery:$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| concat(Master, "-", NodeName) as %"Node Name"
| json field=_raw "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor" as Disk_Space nodrop
| parse regex field=Disk_Space "(?<Disk_Space>.*?) (?<Unit>.*[A-Z]+)" nodrop
| num(Disk_Space)
| if(Unit in ("MB", "Mb", "mb"), Disk_Space/1024, if(Unit in ("KB", "Kb", "kb"), Disk_Space/1024/1024, if(Unit in ("TB", "Tb", "tb"), Disk_Space*1024, Disk_Space))) as Disk_Space
| timeslice 10m
| avg(Disk_Space) as Disk_Space by _timeslice, %"Node Name"
| transpose row _timeslice column %"Node Name"

panels.name: Jenkins Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount,NodeLabel
| _sourceHost as Master
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| json field=Message "nodeName", "monitorData.ArchitectureMonitor", "monitorData.ClockMonitor" ,"monitorData.ResponseTimeMonitor", "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor", "monitorData.TemporarySpaceMonitor", "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "isIdle", "isOnline", "nodeURL", "nodeLabel"  as %"Node Name", Architecture, Clock, %"Reponse Time", %"Disk Space", Temporary_Space, SwapMemory, Idle, Online, URL, %"Node Label" nodrop
| if(Idle matches "true", "false", "true") as Busy
| parse field=SwapMemory "Memory:*  Swap:*" as Physical_Memory, Swap_Memory
| parse regex field=Physical_Memory "(?<Used_Physical_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Physical_Memory>.*?)(?<Unit_Phy>[A-Z]+)"
| num(Used_Physical_Memory) | num(Total_Physical_Memory)
| (Used_Physical_Memory/Total_Physical_Memory)*100 as Used_Physical_Memory
| parse regex field=Swap_Memory "(?<Used_Swap_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Swap_Memory>.*?)(?<Unit_Swap>[A-Z]+)"
| num(Used_Swap_Memory) | num(Total_Swap_Memory)
| (Used_Swap_Memory/Total_Swap_Memory)*100 as Used_Swap_Memory
| if(Total_Physical_Memory=0, "0 %", format("%.2f %s",Used_Physical_Memory, "%")) as %"Used Physical Memory"
| if(Total_Swap_Memory=0, "0 %", format("%.2f %s",Used_Swap_Memory, "%")) as %"Used Swap Memory"
| replace(URL, "(", "%28") as URL
| replace(URL, ")", "%29") as URL
| tourl(URL, %"Node Name") as URL
| count by Master, %"Node Name", %"Node Label", Busy, Online, Architecture, Clock, %"Reponse Time", %"Used Physical Memory", %"Used Swap Memory", %"Disk Space", URL
| fields - _count

panels.name: Executors
panels.queryString:
$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "numberOfExecutors", "nodeName", "nodeLabel", "numberOfFreeExecutors", "eventTime" as Total_Executors, NodeName, NodeLabel, Free_Executors, Event_Time nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| concat(Master, "-",NodeName) as NodeName
| Total_Executors - Free_Executors as Busy_Executors
| first(Total_Executors) as Total_Executors, first(Free_Executors) as Free_Executors, first(Busy_Executors) as Busy_Executors by NodeName
| where Busy_Executors >= 0
| where ![subquery:$$logsrc  Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master
| concat(Master, "-",NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| NodeName as %"Node Name"
| avg(Free_Executors) as %"Free Executors", avg(Busy_Executors) as %"Busy Executors" by %"Node Name"
| fields %"Node Name", %"Free Executors", %"Busy Executors"
